text: The Ernest A. Calling House is a historic house in Gothenburg, Nebraska. It was built by L. J. Anderson in 1907 for Ernest A. Calling, an immigrant from Sweden who first arrived in the United States in 1889, became a businessman in Gothenburg, and died in 1945. With It was designed in the Queen Anne style. It has been listed on the National Register of Historic Places since October 25, 1979. ==References== Category:National Register of Historic Places in Dawson County, Nebraska Category:Queen Anne architecture in Nebraska Category:Houses completed in 1907 Category:1907 establishments in Nebraska
